g-term challenges of chronicling our civic lives, from the actions of small=
-town government in rural America to immigration policy set in Washington, =
D.C.</span></p><p style=3D"Margin-top: 20px;Margin-bottom: 0;">Over all the=
 years I=E2=80=99ve worked here, we=E2=80=99ve given you, our readers, a br=
oader view of politics: =E2=80=9CCoverage on the politics desk at The Conve=
rsation U.S. is not politics the way many Americans think of it =E2=80=93 p=
artisan bickering, horse-trading and he-said-she-said false equivalencies,=
=E2=80=9D we wrote in a=20
manifesto for the desk. =E2=80=9CRather, we cover democracy: what governmen=
t is and how it happens, why it was set up that way, and what the effects a=
re for individual people, various demographic groups and the nation as a wh=
ole.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"Margin-top: 20px;Margin-bottom: 0;">We believe=
 it=E2=80=99s crucial during this time of immense change and conflict to he=
lp readers understand what values and ideals Americans claim to uphold, the=
 processes by which they seek to do that, and the results =E2=80=93 includi=
ng whether they actually uphold or instead undermine those values and ideal=
s.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"Margin-top: 20px;Margin-bottom: 0;">I=E2=80=99ve co=
vered politics for almost 40 years. But sometimes what=E2=80=99s been happe=
ning over the past few years has been so confounding to me that commissioni=
ng and editing a story has been my only way of figuring out what=E2=80=99s =
going on.=20
<strong>That=E2=80=99s the beauty of having researchers write all of The Co=
nversation=E2=80=99s stories.</strong></p><p style=3D"Margin-top: 20px;Marg=
in-bottom: 0;">I am enormously grateful to have had a job in journalism tha=
t has allowed me to ask important questions, and work with fascinating peop=
le to get the answers. These scholars=E2=80=99 intelligence and knowledge h=
as deepened my understanding of the world =E2=80=93 and, I hope, yours. I h=
ave learned so much in this job.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"Margin-top: 20px;Marg=
in-bottom: 0;">Throughout my tenure at The Conversation, my husband and I h=
ave contributed in response to fundraising appeals. We intend to continue t=
hat support.</p><p style=3D"Margin-top: 20px;Margin-bottom: 0;">I hope that=
 you, too, will affirm the value of our work and, by implication, how that =
work helps sustain democracy. <strong>Please consider giving as generously =
as you=20
can</strong>, because you will be investing not just in The Conversation bu=
t in a better-informed public =E2=80=93 and our democracy.&nbsp;</p>
